Purpose: Check OpenSearch posture

177:**Amazon OpenSearch (optional) for searchable note indexing.** For very large charts or when summaries are requested across multi-year histories, indexing all notes into OpenSearch lets you retrieve relevant notes by semantic or keyword search rather than pulling everything and chunking. This is a RAG flavor of summarization: retrieve the most relevant chunks first, then summarize the retrieved set. It trades completeness for scalability and can be appropriate for outpatient longitudinal summaries where "relevant to the current question" is a meaningful filter. If OpenSearch is used, deploy the domain inside the same VPC with VPC-only access (no public endpoint), fine-grained access control enabled, and encryption at rest with a CMK. Reads from Lambda require security-group rules that permit the domain's VPC endpoint.
